# 🧮 DAX Formulas Reference Guide

This document outlines the core Data Analysis Expressions (DAX) used in the Agriculture Packout & Yield Analytics Dashboard. The formulas are structured around best practices, including explicit measure branching, safe division, and custom time intelligence.

---

## 1. Custom Date Dimension (Calendar Table)
Instead of relying on Power BI's auto-date/time feature, a dedicated `Calendar` table was built using DAX. 
**Key Feature:** It includes a continuous `WeekIndex` to ensure that week-over-week (WoW) calculations don't break when crossing over into a new year.

```dax
Calendar = 
VAR BaseCalendar = CALENDARAUTO()
VAR CalculatedTable = 
    GENERATE(
        BaseCalendar,
        VAR BaseDate = [Date]
        RETURN ROW(
            "Year", YEAR(BaseDate),
            "Month", FORMAT(BaseDate, "MMMM"),
            "WeekNumber", WEEKNUM(BaseDate, 2),
            "YearWeek", YEAR(BaseDate) * 100 + WEEKNUM(BaseDate, 2)
        )
    )
RETURN
    // Generates a continuous, unbroken index number for WoW time intelligence
    GENERATE(
        CalculatedTable,
        VAR CurrentYearWeek = [YearWeek]
        RETURN ROW(
            "WeekIndex", RANKX(CalculatedTable, [YearWeek], , ASC, Dense)
        )
    )
. Base Aggregations & Measure Branching
To ensure reusability and prevent users from accidentally using implicit column sums, explicit measures were created for all base metrics. These are then rolled up into a Grand Tot
