. Proportional Distribution Analysis
To find the percentage of the total packout that belongs to a specific size, the DIVIDE function is used. This is preferred over the / operator as it safely handles potential divide-by-zero errors.
// Calculates the percentage of Size L out of the total yield
% L = DIVIDE([Total L], [Grand Total Packout])


// Calculates the percentage of Size M out of the total yield
% M = DIVIDE([Total M], [Grand Total Packout])
Grand Total Packout Last Week = 
VAR CurrentWeekIndex = SELECTEDVALUE('Calendar'[WeekIndex])
RETURN
CALCULATE(
    [Grand Total Packout],
    REMOVEFILTERS('Calendar'),
    'Calendar'[WeekIndex] = CurrentWeekIndex - 1
)

. Week-over-Week (WoW) Time Intelligence
Because agricultural harvest operates on a weekly paking schedule, standart Year-to-date intelingence istnt enough. These measure use the weekidex from the calendar table to dinamically compare the current filtered
week againnst the prior week

Step 1: Retrieve Last Week's Total

Grand Total Packout Last Week = 
VAR CurrentWeekIndex = SELECTEDVALUE('Calendar'[WeekIndex])
RETURN
CALCULATE(
    [Grand Total Packout],
    REMOVEFILTERS('Calendar'),
    'Calendar'[WeekIndex] = CurrentWeekIndex - 1
)

Step 2: Calculate the Variance (Absolute Change)

Packout WoW Variance = 
[Grand Total Packout] - [Grand Total Packout Last Week]

Step 3: Calculate the WoW Growth Percentage

Packout WoW % = 
DIVIDE(
    [Packout WoW Variance],
    [Grand Total Packout Last Week]
)

Usage Note: These measures are desinged to be evaluated within the filter context of the calendar fields if you adapt this model for you own data, ensure your date table has a active,
single direction relationship to tour Fact tableble.

